  "passage": [
    "It is market day long ago—in 1910. Gran takes Eli and Noor to town. The street is made of grey cobblestones. |A horse pulls a wooden cart past the square.",
    "Stalls line the market. A baker in a white apron smiles. |“Fresh bread!” he says. Gran pays two pennies, and the baker wraps a loaf in paper.",
    "Eli sees brass scales on the fruit stall. The seller weighs apples on the scale—one, two, three—and tips them into a basket. |“Fair and even,” says Noor.",
    "Lanterns hang on hooks above the stalls. People chat and swap news. |They walk home over the cobblestones, bread warm in the bag. “Market day is busy and fun!”"
  ],
